-- Slovak Teachers Suspend Strike to Continue Talks, HN Reports
-- B y   R a d o s l a v   T o m e k
-- 2012-11-29T08:04:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-29/slovak-teachers-suspend-strike-to-continue-talks-hn-reports.html
Slovak teachers suspended their
nationwide strike after three days to continue negotiations,
Hospodarske Noviny  reported , citing union leader Pavel Ondek.  Talks with the government over a pay increase will resume,
the newspaper said. Premier  Robert Fico  has ruled out a 10
percent increase in salaries as demanded by the unions,
Hospodarske said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Radoslav Tomek in Bratislava at 
